This #InternationalDanceDay, we have teamed up with the @royalosteosoc to look at how Silver Swans classes, and dancing in general, can be a great way to look after our bone health.

RAD’s Artistic Director, Gerard Charles was in conversation with Sarah Leyland, Clinical Adviser for the Royal Osteoporosis Society and a consultant osteoporosis nurse. Listen to them talk about the benefits of ballet for our overall health, including our bones.

Find your nearest Silver Swans Licensee using the interactive map on our website: www.royalacademyofdance.org/silverswans

#RADSilverSwans #ballet #dance #BoneHealth

node.text:
Throughout 2020 we have all become used to dance in the digital space and our new format for The #Fonteyn2021 gives you early access to coaching without leaving your home town. 

The competition this year will follow a hybrid model of online and in-person experiences, harnessing the best of both worlds and staying true to the creative and collaborative learning ethos of The Fonteyn.

Eligible candidates will receive exclusive one-to-one coaching sessions, online from a range of international professionals, delivered in their teachers’ studios. Candidates will receive a 30-minute coaching session for their Classical Variation and 30 minutes for their Dancer’s Own.

Applications must be received by 24 January 2021, and applicants are advised to sign up as soon as possible to secure the best choice of coaching dates. Visit royalacademyofdance.org/the-fonteyn to learn more.

This clip is from the Genée International Ballet Competition 2018, with gold medallist Monet Hewitt performing the Classical Variation, Raymonda Act II, Variation II.

Step back in time and catch a rare glimpse of RAD’s longest serving President, Dame Margot Fonteyn working behind the scenes to inspire young children taking their first steps in ballet.

This never before seen footage of the Children’s Syllabus, created by Fonteyn with RAD teachers in 1972, shows the first time any of the RAD syllabus was recorded on film. It remained hidden in our archives until it was discovered recently, and will be available to view as part of our display at the @vamuseum. Read more on our website at royalacademyofdance.org

node.text:
The 2021 Members’ Photo Competition winners have been announced!

The overall winner of the competition was a photograph by Jon Raffoul, UK, of L. Apicella-Howard with the caption ‘Dance makes me feel on top of the world’. The judges felt this was a very visually pleasing image, colourful and bright, it conveys the energy and dynamic qualities of dance. It has strong lines echoed by the background. The clever use of shadows adds depth and interest. It is a strong composition and coveys the emotion of dance making her feel on top of the world.

The Luke Rittner Special Commendation goes to a photograph by Vera Stephenson, USA with the caption ‘Dance make me feel like me!’. The judges felt this photograph conveyed what we want everyone to feel about dance. The dancer in the photo shows the purest expression of herself. It is natural, joyful and heartfelt, and shows the emotion of dance making her ‘feel happy to be herself’.

The public choice award attracted 2072 votes and identified the winner as a photograph by Stella Smyrnaki, Greece. It is a stunning photograph that captures ‘dance makes me feel strong’ through the image of a pair of young dancers holding a beautiful pose in front of a mountain landscape.

Read more via the link in bio. 

#ProudToBeRAD

Paloma Hendry Hodson won the silver medal at the Genée (now The Fonteyn) in 2019. In the two years following, Paloma has been working with @thewiggles in Australia. Paloma said: 'we have filmed several series and I have just finished an arena tour around Australia which is amazing, dancing to sold out arenas! I have started the RAD's CBTS programme which I am loving very much, so I can be a fully qualified RAD teacher in the future. I think about the lovely experience I had at the Genée every day, so grateful.'

The #Fonteyn2021 final takes place on Thursday 9 September at 7.30pm BST, ticket holders can watch the event on demand, until 19 September 2021. Book via the link in bio.

🩰 This year, we are inviting audiences from across the world to watch the #Fonteyn2021 final online as dancers compete for the coveted gold, silver and bronze medals. The final takes place on Thursday 9 September at 7.30pm BST, ticket holders can watch the event on demand, until 19 September 2021.

Hosted by @darceybussellofficial and RAD Artistic Director, Gerard Charles, this special online event will also provide a unique insight behind the scenes with interviews with famed dancers such as @leannebenjamin_official, Dame Monica Mason and a rare glimpse into the competition process. Click the link in our bio to book.
